idn&#039;t work well with Avada</h4>\n				<div class="star-rating"><div class="wporg-ratings" aria-label="2 из 5 звезд" data-title-template="%s из 5 звезд" data-rating="2" style="color:#ffb900;"><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-filled"></span><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-filled"></span><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-empty"></span><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-empty"></span><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-empty"></span></div></div>\n			</div>\n			<p class="reviewer">\n				By <a href="https://profiles.wordpress.org/lpblue"><img alt='''' src=''https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/943866b36415daa2bfc1c6a729b9a565?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g'' srcset=''https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/943866b36415daa2bfc1c6a729b9a565?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x'' class=''avatar avatar-16 photo'' height=''16'' width=''16'' /></a><a href="https://profiles.wordpress.org/lpblue" class="reviewer-name">blue <small>(lpblue)</small></a> on <span class="review-date">July 30, 2017</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class="review-body">I was disappointed at the display options since Avada recommended this plugin. This plugin creates a separate huge page of lengthy options for each event, which isn''t optimal for the site I''m working on. Too complex for entering simple new events, and there aren''t any easy customizations to make it compact and concise. I don''t like the navigation on the event pages at all and need something much more straightforward and intuitive.</div>\n</div>\n<div class="review">\n	<div class="review-head">\n		<div class="reviewer-info">\n			<div class="review-title-section">\n				<h4 class="review-title">Waste of HOURS of Time</h4>\n				<div class="star-rating"><div class="wporg-ratings" aria-label="1 из 5 звезд" data-title-template="%s из 5 звезд" data-rating="1" style="color:#ffb900;"><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-filled"></span><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-empty"></span><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-empty"></span><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-empty"></span><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-empty"></span></div></div>\n			</div>\n			<p class="reviewer">\n				By <a href="https://profiles.wordpress.org/solmage"><img alt='''' src=''https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/26ba667d65e15c92bbf537fe72d25330?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g'' srcset=''https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/26ba667d65e15c92bbf537fe72d25330?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x'' class=''avatar avatar-16 photo'' height=''16'' width=''16'' /></a><a href="https://profiles.wordpress.org/solmage" class="reviewer-name">SolMage</a> on <span class="review-date">July 30, 2017</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class="review-body">I''ve spent more than an hour trying to make this plug-in work. The calendar view doesn''t show any excerpt text -- or whites it all out so no one can see it. I''ve installed, reinstalled, updated theme, etc -- all to no avail. I''ll be hunting for a plug in that works.</div>\n</div>\n<div class="review">\n	<div class="review-head">\n		<div class="reviewer-info">\n			<div class="review-title-section">\n				<h4 class="review-title">Free version not compatible with pro version after 1 year</h4>\n				<div class="star-rating"><div class="wporg-ratings" aria-label="1 из 5 звезд" data-title-template="%s из 5 звезд" data-rating="1" style="color:#ffb900;"><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-filled"></span><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-empty"></span><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-empty"></span><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-empty"></span><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-empty"></span></div></div>\n			</div>\n			<p class="reviewer">\n				By <a href="https://profiles.wordpress.org/nikkoboy"><img alt='''' src=''https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/f7a3e38977599f1daf3d27d27d9ae8f6?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g'' srcset=''https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/f7a3e38977599f1daf3d27d27d9ae8f6?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x'' class=''avatar avatar-16 photo'' height=''16'' width=''16'' /></a><a href="https://profiles.wordpress.org/nikkoboy" class="reviewer-name">nikkoboy</a> on <span class="review-date">July 27, 2017</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class="review-body">I don''t appreciate the eventcalendar''s commercial policy of rendering older versions of theeventcalendar pro obsolete, so they can cash in ($80) every year, once the free version of theeventcalendar plugin isn''t compatible anymore with the pro version. That''s basically taking your pro users hostage (while you should be thanking them for paying a premium!). And I don''t feel like renewing my pro licence every year, just to avoid being in this situation. Really unprofessional.</div>\n</div>\n<div class="review">\n	<div class="review-head">\n		<div class="reviewer-info">\n			<div class="review-title-section">\n				<h4 class="review-title">Tolle Sache</h4>\n				<div class="star-rating"><div class="wporg-ratings" aria-label="5 из 5 звезд" data-title-template="%s из 5 звезд" data-rating="5" style="color:#ffb900;"><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-filled"></span><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-filled"></span><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-filled"></span><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-filled"></span><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-filled"></span></div></div>\n			</div>\n			<p class="reviewer">\n				By <a href="https://profiles.wordpress.org/donredhorse"><img alt='''' src=''https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/4d0550f4c9a06de205c9959593e08486?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g'' srcset=''https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/4d0550f4c9a06de205c9959593e08486?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x'' class=''avatar avatar-16 photo'' height=''16'' width=''16'' /></a><a href="https://profiles.wordpress.org/donredhorse" class="reviewer-name">donredhorse</a> on <span class="review-date">July 23, 2017</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class="review-body">Ich nutze das Plugin für eine Vereins-Website. Einige Dinge könnten verbessert oder optimiert werden, aber für ein kostenfreies Plugin ist "The Event Calendar" eine schöne Lösung. Vielen Dank!</div>\n</div>\n<div class="review">\n	<div class="review-head">\n		<div class="reviewer-info">\n			<div class="review-title-section">\n				<h4 class="review-title">Excelente plugin!!!!</h4>\n				<div class="star-rating"><div class="wporg-ratings" aria-label="5 из 5 звезд" data-title-template="%s из 5 звезд" data-rating="5" style="color:#ffb900;"><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-filled"></span><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-filled"></span><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-filled"></span><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-filled"></span><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-filled"></span></div></div>\n			</div>\n			<p class="reviewer">\n				By <a href="https://profiles.wordpress.org/rbraile"><img alt='''' src=''https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/b279cbd36dedf3cdea30f4d85111b15e?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g'' srcset=''https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/b279cbd36dedf3cdea30f4d85111b15e?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x'' class=''avatar avatar-16 photo'' height=''16'' width=''16'' /></a><a href="https://profiles.wordpress.org/rbraile" class="reviewer-name">rbraile</a> on <span class="review-date">July 22, 2017</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class="review-body">Muy buen plugin funciono a la perfección desde el principio, con muchas opciones de personalización excelente muy recomendable</div>\n</div>\n<div class="review">\n	<div class="review-head">\n		<div class="reviewer-info">\n			<div class="review-title-section">\n				<h4 class="review-title">Needs More Work As It&#039;s Not Fully Customizable</h4>\n				<div class="star-rating"><div class="wporg-ratings" aria-label="1 из 5 звезд" data-title-template="%s из 5 звезд" data-rating="1" style="color:#ffb900;"><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-filled"></span><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-empty"></span><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-empty"></span><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-empty"></span><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-empty"></span></div></div>\n			</div>\n			<p class="reviewer">\n				By <a href="https://profiles.wordpress.org/tannetoni"><img alt='''' src=''https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/748367b5d82964ec21a471357d2c75f9?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g'' srcset=''https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/748367b5d82964ec21a471357d2c75f9?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x'' class=''avatar avatar-16 photo'' height=''16'' width=''16'' /></a><a href="https://profiles.wordpress.org/tannetoni" class="reviewer-name">tannetoni</a> on <span class="review-date">July 18, 2017</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class="review-body">The Events Calendar plugin came with the Avada theme - which I use quite a bit. This is the first time I''ve used the Events Calendar plugin and although a nice idea, it falls short in a couple areas for me. \n\nFor one, there is no option for showcasing future events that do not have dates specified yet. For example, let''s say you have 24 events and 4 of them are in discussion and you haven''t locked in specific dates yet. In this case, you''d want to still showcase the events, but use "TBA" or "TBD" to show that the dates aren''t yet determined. Unfortunately, the Events Calendar plugin does not offer a "TBA" and "TBD" option. Instead, it requires you to put in dates, and if you don''t, it defaults to the current date. \n\nWhen I brought this to the attention of the plugin developers, they said they don''t have this option but I could vote on requesting it. I think I was vote number 54 but the post had been there for a couple of years - either way, 54 votes isn''t significant enough to the developers to add this functionality. Which is odd to me considering that events on a large scale would absolutely utilize this feature. Furthermore, why wouldn''t you want to add as much functionality as possible to make your plugin the best event plugin around? It''s called competitive advantage!\n\nThe other place this plugin falls short is that it auto creates your event page - where the events will show up. This page is NOT customizable. You can change the url, but you cannot style your page. As a web designer/developer, I HATE it when there is little customization options and I know how to code! So for the everyday user who doesn''t know how to code, this plugin gives them little flexibility. As users, we should have full control over how we want our pages to look so not having this option is terrible. \n\nThese options aren''t even available in the Pro version - so why would anyone upgrade?  I''m in search of a plugin that does offer these - or at least where the developers are interested in listening to their users and adding these functionalities.  </div>\n</div>\n<div class="review">\n	<div class="review-head">\n		<div class="reviewer-info">\n			<div class="review-title-section">\n				<h4 class="review-title">Don&#039;t work in combination with woocommerce, no support</h4>\n				<div class="star-rating"><div class="wporg-ratings" aria-label="1 из 5 звезд" data-title-template="%s из 5 звезд" data-rating="1" style="color:#ffb900;"><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-filled"></span><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-empty"></span><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-empty"></span><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-empty"></span><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-empty"></span></div></div>\n			</div>\n			<p class="reviewer">\n				By <a href="https://profiles.wordpress.org/ole_wilkenburg"><img alt='''' src=''https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/fa5fe75f1bab214312dedb1157182fcd?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g'' srcset=''https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/fa5fe75f1bab214312dedb1157182fcd?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x'' class=''avatar avatar-16 photo'' height=''16'' width=''16'' /></a><a href="https://profiles.wordpress.org/ole_wilkenburg" class="reviewer-name">ole_wilkenburg</a> on <span class="review-date">July 12, 2017</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class="review-body">Internal Server Error 500 when I try to access the woocommerce orders page. When you plugin is activated, if not the page works fine.</div>\n</div>\n<div class="review">\n	<div class="review-head">\n		<div class="reviewer-info">\n			<div class="review-title-section">\n				<h4 class="review-title">Muy bueno</h4>\n				<div class="star-rating"><div class="wporg-ratings" aria-label="5 из 5 звезд" data-title-template="%s из 5 звезд" data-rating="5" style="color:#ffb900;"><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-filled"></span><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-filled"></span><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-filled"></span><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-filled"></span><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-filled"></span></div></div>\n			</div>\n			<p class="reviewer">\n				By <a href="https://profiles.wordpress.org/angelspaz"><img alt='''' src=''https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/a69070379c645f23927f486e0d53b7a9?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g'' srcset=''https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/a69070379c645f23927f486e0d53b7a9?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x'' class=''avatar avatar-16 photo'' height=''16'' width=''16'' /></a><a href="https://profiles.wordpress.org/angelspaz" class="reviewer-name">angelspaz</a> on <span class="review-date">July 7, 2017</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class="review-body">Excelente</div>\n</div>\n<div class="review">\n	<div class="review-head">\n		<div class="reviewer-info">\n			<div class="review-title-section">\n				<h4 class="review-title">Great Events plugin</h4>\n				<div class="star-rating"><div class="wporg-ratings" aria-label="5 из 5 звезд" data-title-template="%s из 5 звезд" data-rating="5" style="color:#ffb900;"><span class="star dashicons dashicons-star-filled"></span><span class="star dashicons das